            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "For custom entry points you could mention that there is one good way to avoid unrecoverable reloader crashes:\r\n\r\n- have imports for the cli entrypoint without side effects (e.g. `yourpackage.cli`, with `yourpackage/__init__.py` being empty-ish and `yourpackage.cli` having no global imports of other application stuff or anything else not absolutely necessary)\r\n- use another package/module like `yourpackage_cli` as the entry point for the CLI, so any error when importing in `yourpackage` will not happen at CLI import time"
        },
